def solve (y, x, Q, S):
    # Write your code 
    
    raise ValueError(S, x, y)
    l=[(0,0)]
    for i in range(len(S)):
        if S[i]=='U':
            l.append( (l[-1][0], l[-1][1] +1) )
        elif S[i]=='D':
            l.append( (l[-1][0], l[-1][1] -1) )
        elif S[i]=='R':
            l.append( (l[-1][0]+1, l[-1][1]) )
        elif S[i]=='L':
            l.append( (l[-1][0]-1, l[-1][1]) )
    out_=0
    
    q=[]
    
    for i in range(len(y)):
        q.append((x[i], y[i]))
    
    for i in range(len(l)):
        for j in range(i+1, len(l)):
            if (l[j][0]-l[i][0], l[j][1]-l[i][1]) in q:
                out_+=1
                q.remove((l[j][0]-l[i][0], l[j][1]-l[i][1]))
    return out_
